Result: 0 exact duplicates found.
Hypothesis: Unique Loan IDs or trailing spaces in categorical columns may be masking near-duplicates. Will re-verify after the Trimming phase."


Re Checked the duplicate removal and took away the unique identifiers to find there were several duplicates actually and the data amount changed.
"During Phase 2 (ETL), an initial deduplication check returned 0 matches. However, after performing data normalization (Trimming/Cleaning),
a second pass identified 18,527 duplicate records. These were removed to ensure the integrity of the final analysis."

Data Integrity Note: Handling NAICS Code '0'

Discovery: 201,655 records (approx. 22.4% of the dataset) contained a '0' entry for the NAICS industry code.

Decision: Retained all records. Deleting them would have caused a significant under-reporting of the total loan volume.

Action: Re-classified '0' as "Unknown Industry" to ensure accurate financial totals while maintaining clear boundaries for industry-specific analysis.

Note the Migration: "Segmented 500k rows of zero-value NAICS data into yearly sub-sheets (1962–2018)."

Note the System Optimization: "Implemented file-splitting to resolve hardware resource exhaustion and network latency issues."
